</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvespid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vespid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/01 12:24:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: First Attempt went badly, need advice</span><hr size=1> I started quad kiting around 25 or so.  I was twinked out the a$$ though.<br>
<br>
25-30 - Goblins, Sarnaks, Skeles just over the hill from the backdoor in LIO.<br>
<br>
30-34 - Camped a static spawn.<br>
<br>
34-42 - Dire wolves in Iceclad near the iceflows / dragon circle.<br>
<br>
You can supposedly quad dire wovles till about 45, but that seemed pointless with the exp.<br>
<br>
I didn't need to snare at all for any of these mobs.  In fact taking the time to snare probably slowed me down (resists, rounding up, yadda yadda yadda).<br>
<br>
Even with wolves you have enough time to get out of range, stop, turn a little to avoid an interrupt, cast, then start running again before they smack you down.<br>
<br>
It's REALLY close though -- not recommended for the easily frightened or dial-up connections. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Best of luck. <p><img src="http://ns.iicanada.com/scott/pimp.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 7:20:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Reason I snare</span><hr size=1> I snare so that folk will have another clue that everything is fine and things are under control.<br>
<br>
Hell you can outrun unsnared dire wolves WITHOUT SoW, so certainly you don't need snare if you are sowed.<br>
<br>
It does seem to help keep them grouped a little though.<br>
<br>
Also want to add my /disagree to Nords re not quadding till 51, it's good to do well before that. /agree to Nords re getting flux staff, it is invaluable.<br>
<br>
Also Danenel even if you get jboots, I wouldn't use them, too slow. Buy sow potions for quadding and use the boots for travelling.<br>
<br>
FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvespid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vespid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 9:58:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reason I snare</span><hr size=1> 1. Flux staff rocks.<br>
<br>
2. It should be your responsibility to make sure your quad kites are out of other people's way, and I never bothered to waste time and mana to make people feel more comfortable with what I was doing (since I never came near them).  This is really only a problem at lower levels.<br>
<br>
3. Why on earth would you waste good money on SOW potions when jboots work just fine?  For travelling, perhaps, but for 60 seconds of quad kiting and 10 minutes of sitting on yer ass? <p><img src="http://ns.iicanada.com/scott/pimp.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umacksin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Macksin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 11:14:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> JBoots vs Potions</span><hr size=1> There's a very good reason.  I am not sure at what level JBoots casts SOW, but it is slower than the SOW potions I get from a 35 + shamman.  <br>
<br>
I'll check with my shamman friends, but I do believe the SOW potions work as a spell cast by the current level of the shamman that made them, while JBoots work as cast by someone under 20th level.<br>
<br>
That's my 2 coppers<br>
<br>
Later<br>
<br>
Macksin Shadizar<br>
36th level Wizard<br>
Merciless Justice (www.mercjustice.com)<br>
Veeshan Server<br>
<br>
&quot;If it makes you feel better to call it evil, so be it.  I have no such illusions.  I am here simply to blow stuff up!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 11:43:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: JBoots vs Potions</span><hr size=1> I find the increase in speed to be worth it. Granted it is not needed for many mobs. Some mobs are just plain fast, like recently when I was kiting snow griffs for the eggs. But you're right for most mobs it's not necessary, I just like the comfort factor. Probably that's another reason I snare, I like the security of it.<br>
<br>
As far as people interfering, there's nowhere you can be sure of there being no other people. That's why this is a MMORPG not a CFRPG. You can reduce the risk of other people interfering but not eliminate it.<br>
<br>
At lvl 40 I find there are a LOT of people who don't know how to behave around quadders. (ie leave us ALONE) I hope this improves.<br>
<br>
FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvespid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vespid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 5:25:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: JBoots vs Potions</span><hr size=1> Sounds to me like lower level quadding has more style preferences than 51+ quadding.  Too bad most wizzies don't find out about it earlier (low level quad kiting was far more fun for me than at my current level).<br>
<br>
J-boot speed is the lowest SOW in the game, if I remember correctly (equiv to level 9 shaman SOW).  I just really have never needed more than that to quad. <p><img src="http://ns.iicanada.com/scott/pimp.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/4/01 9:39:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: JBoots vs Potions</span><hr size=1> I can say quadding is GREAT fun stil at 40. I did some calcs, and it should be doable from level *8*, if you had sow potion or jboots (or now tboots). A well twinked wiz could really breeze thru levels.<br>
<br>
If they only made BUYABLE clarity potoins..<br>
<br>
As for bubbas.. last night, yet again... I saw a Druid root kiting elites. He came upon me, and he snared my last drakkel for faction (he didn't see me kiting the other 3) so, to be nice, I told him, look, just buff or little heal ME when I am almost thru and you can get faction for all 4 (we had the &quot;you had FOUR?&quot; discussion) I will tell you when, wait for them to be almost dead! So I gather them up, get them snared, and before I land my first CoF, he CHLOROPLASTS me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Of course two wolves veer off after him, so I just gated, and pulled elsewhere after that. He had to waste mana on four greens, and I wasted 5 minutes herding. So he lost out on easy faction all night long, (he was deep in a faction hole) but I can't quad around ppl that are unpredictable, even though he seemed like a nice guy.<br>
<br>
FK<br>
